<li><i><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.gutenberg.net/etext/333">Robert Louis Stevenson</a></i>, a biography by Sir <a href="Walter_Raleigh_(professor)" title="Walter Raleigh (professor)">Walter Alexander Raleigh</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://books.google.com/books?vid=OCLC00502469&id=8omQokmMv7IC&pg=RA1-PA287&lpg=RA1-PA287&dq=stevenson+inauthor:edmund+inauthor:gosse&num=100#PRA1-PA275,M1">Robert Louis Stevenson: a memoir</a> (1895), by <a href="Edmund_Gosse" title="Edmund Gosse">Edmund Gosse</a> who knew Stevenson personally</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://books.google.com/books?hl=en&id=ahwOAAAAIAAJ&dq=graham+balfour+life+of+robert+louis+stevenson&printsec=frontcover&source=web&ots=bWzWrnfJ6J&sig=3ulX-IRZwmlKtqA9FyLn7fHtSdQ">The Life of Robert Louis Stevenson</a> (1913) by Graham Balfour, Stevenson's cousin.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Robert_Louis_Stevenson:_a_short_biography" class="extiw" title="s:Robert Louis Stevenson: a short biography">Robert Louis Stevenson: biography</a> (1911), by <a href="Edmund_Gosse" title="Edmund Gosse">Edmund Gosse</a>, from the <i><a href="Encyclop%C3%A6dia_Britannica_Eleventh_Edition" title="Encyclopædia Britannica Eleventh Edition">Encyclopædia Britannica Eleventh Edition</a></i></li>
